We connect users to third-party services (SimpleSwap, Rango Exchange) who perform actual swaps/bridges.

## 2. Geographic Restrictions
Our services are NOT available in:
- China, Egypt, Iraq, Qatar, Morocco, Algeria, Bangladesh, Nepal, Bolivia

Additional restrictions may apply based on local laws.

## 3. User Responsibilities
Users are responsible for:
- Compliance with local tax laws
- Verifying legality in their jurisdiction
- Understanding crypto risks
- Securing their own wallets

## 4. Risk Disclosure
Cryptocurrency trading involves substantial risk:
- Price volatility
- Loss of entire investment possible
- Smart contract risks
- Bridge security risks
- Network congestion delays

## 5. No Financial Advice
YageCoin provides technology tools only. We do NOT provide:
- Investment advice
- Tax advice
- Legal advice

Consult professionals for financial decisions.

## 6. KYC/AML
We do not collect KYC. However, third-party services (SimpleSwap, Rango) may have their own KYC requirements which users must comply with.

## 7. Token Disclaimer (YGCT)
YGCT tokens:
- Are utility tokens, not securities
- Provide platform benefits only
- Have no guaranteed value
- Are not investment contracts
- May have zero value

## 8. Limitation of Liability
YageCoin is not liable for:
- Third-party service failures
- Transaction losses
- Smart contract bugs
- User errors
- Market movements

## 9. Age Requirement
Users must be 18+ or legal age in their jurisdiction.

## 10. Changes to Terms
We reserve right to update these terms. Continued use = acceptance.

Last Updated: [Date]

